{
  "text": "Gram-staining was performed by the modified Hucker method according to Gerhardt et al. [CITATION_1] . Cell morphology was investigated by light microscopy at 1000\u00c2 magnification with a Leica DFC 3000G microscope and glass slides covered with 2 % (w/v) agar (Becton Dickinson) that had been washed three times (each time for 20 min in pure water) and autoclaved. Cell size was measured with the LAS X (Leica) software. The presence of capsules based on EPS production was determined by contrasting a bacterial suspension with china ink; M. paludis VKM B-2446",
